						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone fixed into the front wall of the Hanumān temple near the village Chāvaḍi.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 1644.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1566, Tāraṇa, Srāvaṇa, śu. 1 Friday.</hi> The <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> corresponds to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1644, July 24,</hi> when the weekday was Wednesday instead of Friday.</p>						

						<p>The inscription, in Nāgari characters and Marāṭhī language, seems to record the construction of Hanumān temple, in stone, and a gift of land made for it.</p>						

						</summary>
